SSyynnooppssiiss
       cc [options] file -lcurses #include <curses.h>

       void idcok(WINDOW *win, bool bf);

DDeessccrriippttiioonn
       The  function specifies whether the implementation may use
       hardware insert- and delete-character features in  win  if
       the  terminal is so equipped.  If bf is TRUE, use of these
       features in win is enabled.  If bf is FALSE, use of  these
       features in win is disabled.  The initial state is TRUE.

RReettuurrnn vvaalluuee
       The function does not return a value.

EErrrroorrss
       No errors are defined.

